order\u003C/a\u003E by Maarten Baert.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHave you tried Firefox with plugins disabled?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEdit: I also thought you meant \u0027liking\u0027 posts, I\u0027ll try the votes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEdit2: Yes it appears you\u0027re right, I don\u0027t see a way to remove the vote.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dman979","CreatedById":123837,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-08T18:46:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222914628\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022154662\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221483894282\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002216426\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sal_vager\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, sal_vager said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEdit: I also thought you meant \u0027liking\u0027 posts, I\u0027ll try the votes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWelp, looks like we all just learned something about clarity in writing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-09T06:19:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222914626\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022154662\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221483894180\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022123837\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Dman979\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 hours ago, Dman979 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/73725-5thhorseman/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002273725\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/73725-5thhorseman/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@5thHorseman\u003C/a\u003E- I wasn\u0027t referring to the \u0022Like this\u0022 button, I meant the arrow. Is that what you did, too?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh no I didn\u0027t try that, sorry.\u00A0 Let me now...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI can \u0022unupvote\u0022 before hitting refresh but not after. If I upvote a thread and \u0022unupvote\u0022 it, I cannot upvote it again until I *DO* refresh the page. This seems consistent across posts and I agree - it makes no sense so sounds buggish.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222914758\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022154662\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221483901178\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022123837\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Dman979\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 hours ago, Dman979 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWelp, looks like we all just learned something about clarity in writing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think it says more about how much we use the upvoting system over (or in this case under) the \u0022Like\u0022 system. I personally don\u0027t like the upvoting system for answers because it breaks the flow of conversation in a thread in a nonobvious way.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}